Thugs raided the home of a National Youth Service official in Amagoro area and made away with 31 head of cattle valued at Sh700, 000. Acting Chief Mr Edwin Lijodi said that during the raid on Mr Evans Kundu&#39;s home on Friday, the gang drove away the animals towards Moi&#39;s Bridge before residents tracked them down and recovered 28 animals. Lijodi has now urged residents to be vigilant and use social media platforms to pass on information when cattle thefts occur.&nbsp;